        "text": "Exodus 39:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It was made of fine linen; tradition describes it as 24 ft. long, so it was probably wound round the head like a turban. Besides the passages quoted, where it denotes the headdress of the high priest, it occurs only in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
