        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the golden plate, the holy crown",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The golden plate is described ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:36-37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Heb. word (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ẓîẓ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), translated ‘plate,’ implies something bright and glittering, and is elsewhere used of a flower. The plate was fastened by its lace of blue to the turban (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
