        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 39:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and would appear as an ornament or diadem in the headgear of the high priest. It is called ‘the holy crown’ in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and here both names are given to it. The same combination occurs in ",
        "children": []
